50|$|Abigail Becker (1830-1905), {{known as}} the Angel of Long Point, was a Canadian woman {{credited}} with saving the lives of numerous sailors caught in <b>storms</b> along <b>the</b> shores of Long Point. <b>When</b> <b>the</b> <b>storms</b> had passed, she would wade in the water {{as far as she}} could to rescue trapped seamen from their doomed ships.|$|R
