50|$|In Kōchi Prefecture, where <b>the</b> <b>storm</b> {{first made}} landfall, {{powerful}} wind gusts—measured up to 234 km/h—caused tremendous damage. Torrential rain accompanied <b>the</b> <b>storm.</b> Throughout Kōchi, 1,815 homes were destroyed and 6,064 were damaged or flooded; 81 people died and 399 more sustained injuries. Sixty-three {{people died in}} Muroto <b>when</b> <b>the</b> typhoon's <b>storm</b> surge swept away 550 homes.|$|R
